        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 16. Kamilocella latilabris (Reuss). (a) MMG SaK 1615; late Cenomanian, Hoher Stein Quarry in Dresden-Plauen, Saxony, Germany; autozooids (some ovicellate) and an avicularium (lower left). (b– d) NHMUK BZ 8215; late Cenomanian or early Turonian, Kaňk, Central Bohemian Region, Czech Republic; (b) part of a bifoliate colony; (c) autozooids and two avicularia; (d) ovicellate autozooid and an avicularium. Scale bars: a = 300 µm; b = 500 µm; c = 200 µm; d = 100 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747179/files/figure.png" .

